    "title": "Linear Inequalities",
    "body": "Solve an inequality like an equation, but remember one rule: if you multiply or divide both sides by a negative number, flip the inequality sign. The solution is a range of values, not a single one.",
    "key_points": [
      "Isolate the variable as with equations.",
      "Flip the sign when multiplying/dividing by a negative.",
      "≤ and ≥ include the endpoint; < and > do not."
